Class GameEvent

java.lang.Object
model.GameEvent
public class GameEvent extends Object
GameEvent

Represents an event that occurs during a soccer match. Examples of events include goals, assists, fouls, cards, etc.

Contains information about the event, including the match, player, type, and time.

Example usage: 

 GameEvent event = new GameEvent();
 GameEvent goalEvent = new GameEvent(1, 101, 5, "Goal", 23);

    • GameEvent

      public GameEvent(int eventId, int matchId, int playerId, String eventType, int eventTime)
      Parameterized constructor.
      Parameters:
      eventId - the unique ID of the event
      matchId - the ID of the match where the event occurred
      playerId - the ID of the player involved in the event
      eventType - the type of event (e.g., "Goal", "Assist", "Yellow Card")
      eventTime - the minute in the match when the event occurred
